{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0af55443-5272-4e69-9c7c-606dfdc8a49e","content":"The `dump-collect` skill I have available is specifically for **collecting** crash dumps, not analyzing them. For **analyzing** a `.dmp` file, here are the recommended tools:\n\n### `dotnet-dump analyze`\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze <path-to-dump.dmp>\n```\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack\n- `pe` (print exception) — last exception details\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all threads\n\n### LLDB (Linux)\n```bash\ndotnet symbol --output /tmp/symbols <path-to-dump.dmp>\nlldb --core <path-to-dump.dmp>\n```\n\n### Visual Studio (Windows)\nOpen the `.dmp` file directly — it provides a rich GUI for inspection.\n\n---\n\nWould you like me to install `dotnet-dump` and start analyzing the file here? If so, share the path to your `.dmp` file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d8888152-1a0a-41ab-9140-4925bdbddb77","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description specifically says:\n\n- USE FOR: enabling automatic crash dumps, capturing dumps, setting up dump collection\n- DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\n\nSo the `dump-collect` skill is NOT appropriate here. The user wants to analyze a dump, not collect one.\n\nLet me help them directly with guidance on analyzing crash dumps.","outputTokens":386,"requestId":"D80C:165916:5D2FAE2:65303E3:69FBF1BE"},"id":"c078813c-4e50-42af-b044-9337ab6dd4ba","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:58:32.835Z","parentId":"98e3f0fa-9037-4bc0-961b-5ccfe25ec3ba"}
